  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">With the funds, the Sekere Community Youth Association will work with the Sekere community to address waste from local pig farms contaminating the community&apos;s primary water sources. Many pigpens had been built on the riverbanks in Sekere and their waste is contaminating waterways. The association will use the funds to raise awareness about the importance of relocating the pens and converting them to dry litter systems to prevent future contamination; organize cleanup activities; and develop long term plans and partnerships. The funds will help the group apply for additional funds from the UN GEF Small Grants Program that will establish a fund for farmers relocating and converting their pigpens.</narrative>
  </description>
